-- Thomson Reuters Paid About $40 Million for Zawya, National Says
-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2012-06-26T06:46:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/thomson-reuters-paid-about-40-million-for-zawya-national-says.html
Thomson Reuters  Corp. paid about $40
million for Zawya Ltd., which provides online business
information on the Middle East and North Africa, Abu Dhabi-based
 The National  reported, citing people it did not identify.  Thomson Reuters announced the acquisition of Dubai-based
Zawya yesterday without disclosing the value of the deal.  Bloomberg LP, the parent of Bloomberg News, competes with
Thomson Reuters in selling financial and legal information and
trading systems.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Arif Sharif in Dubai at 
 asharif2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  